# Tavily API Skill

- When writing code that requires web search or "Literature QC", use the Tavily API.
- The Tavily API expects a POST request to `https://api.tavily.com/search`.
- Always pass the API key via the `process.env.TAVILY_API_KEY` environment variable.
- For the "Literature QC" step, configure the Tavily payload to prefer academic or scientific sources (e.g., using `include_domains: ["protocols.io", "nature.com", "ncbi.nlm.nih.gov"]` if applicable).
- Ensure the API route returns a strict JSON structure containing: `noveltySignal` ("not found", "similar work exists", "exact match found") and an array of `references`.